1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,167
They brought us breakfast in the morning, like cheese and rice

2
00:00:06,167 --> 00:00:09,542
Within reasonable limits

3
00:00:11,083 --> 00:00:16,125
Many people would come in the morning and leave at noon

4
00:00:16,167 --> 00:00:20,167
They were transferred elsewhere or released, we didn’t know about these things

5
00:00:21,751 --> 00:00:26,292
Interviewer: As for medical supplies

6
00:00:27,334 --> 00:00:29,375
Were they available in this place?

7
00:00:29,751 --> 00:00:33,834
It never happened that I experienced this matter

8
00:00:33,918 --> 00:00:39,125
Interviewer: What didn’t you experience? Witness: Treatment

9
00:00:39,751 --> 00:00:40,959
It never happened to me

10
00:00:42,209 --> 00:00:45,876
But I think whoever was suffering was taken to the hospital

11
00:00:46,167 --> 00:00:48,083
If their condition was serious

12
00:00:48,459 --> 00:00:51,375
This is just a holding prison, no need for supplies

13
00:00:52,584 --> 00:00:55,667
Whoever had a serious case was transferred to another prison

14
00:00:55,959 --> 00:01:00,876
There is a prison in Meydan they would transfer them to

15
00:01:01,334 --> 00:01:04,250
And in the church there were also prisoners

16
00:01:04,292 --> 00:01:06,167
It became a prison

17
00:01:06,792 --> 00:01:08,792
We didn’t know what was happening

18
00:01:08,876 --> 00:01:12,834
And sometimes we heard screams from torture and flogging

19
00:01:13,042 --> 00:01:17,083
We didn’t know what was going on because we were behind closed doors

20
00:01:17,751 --> 00:01:20,334
We didn’t know what was happening outside, or see it

21
00:01:21,083 --> 00:01:24,667
Interviewer: When you were here

22
00:01:24,751 --> 00:01:29,083
In this group cell

23
00:01:30,125 --> 00:01:31,417
Did you hear any sounds?

24
00:01:31,959 --> 00:01:35,834
At night we used to hear the sounds of beating and torture

25
00:01:36,083 --> 00:01:37,709
But we didn’t know what they were

26
00:01:39,959 --> 00:01:44,792
One time they took someone from us and he never came back

27
00:01:45,375 --> 00:01:48,876
Whether they released him or killed him, we didn’t know

28
00:01:50,834 --> 00:01:53,459
Interviewer: How did you feel when you heard those sounds?

29
00:01:53,542 --> 00:01:55,792
We felt fear, we didn’t know what our fate would be

30
00:01:55,876 --> 00:01:58,292
Whether we would die, be flogged, or thrown away

31
00:01:58,334 --> 00:02:02,417
Three quarters of those they took were killed

32
00:02:02,417 --> 00:02:06,292
Even our thinking became confused because we didn’t know our fate

33
00:02:06,959 --> 00:02:09,334
Whether they would release us or kill us

34
00:02:09,626 --> 00:02:11,584
We didn’t know

35
00:02:12,417 --> 00:02:17,667
Interviewer: When you were here

36
00:02:18,250 --> 00:02:21,709
Was the prison ever bombed?

37
00:02:22,083 --> 00:02:27,500
No, we just heard the sound of planes

38
00:02:27,959 --> 00:02:32,834
And we were terrified they might bomb the prison at any moment

39
00:02:33,209 --> 00:02:36,125
At night the planes were intense, we could hear them

40
00:02:37,042 --> 00:02:38,834
And it went on like that

41
00:02:41,792 --> 00:02:46,584
Interviewer: Tell us about the prisoners who were with you

42
00:02:46,667 --> 00:02:49,375
How was the relationship between you inside the prison?

43
00:02:49,500 --> 00:02:54,292
As I told you from the start, when they brought us in

44
00:02:55,042 --> 00:02:59,626
We greeted each other, and at prayer time one of us would lead

45
00:03:02,209 --> 00:03:05,834
Each person would tell what he was charged with, smoking or something else

46
00:03:05,834 --> 00:03:11,167
We didn’t know everyone, and one of them could be an informant for them

47
00:03:11,626 --> 00:03:15,584
Pretending to complain to make you speak against them

48
00:03:15,918 --> 00:03:17,167
And you’d be held accountable for what you said

49
00:03:18,334 --> 00:03:19,959
So you’d see each of us by himself

50
00:03:20,334 --> 00:03:24,918
They’d give us a paper to read

51
00:03:25,667 --> 00:03:29,584
Our fate and life were exhausting

52
00:03:30,959 --> 00:03:34,709
Interviewer: Let’s talk about the washrooms

53
00:03:35,667 --> 00:03:38,626
Were cleaning supplies available in the washrooms?

54
00:03:38,626 --> 00:03:43,626
There was only laundry soap

55
00:03:44,876 --> 00:03:47,918
The washrooms were here inside

56
00:03:49,334 --> 00:03:53,667
Interviewer: You mean they were available? Witness: Yes

57
00:03:54,292 --> 00:03:56,417
Interviewer: And what about showering?

58
00:03:56,918 --> 00:04:01,083
Did you use to shower?

59
00:04:01,125 --> 00:04:06,459
No, there were only washrooms for laundry

60
00:04:06,542 --> 00:04:11,250
This was a shower and toilet

61
00:04:11,751 --> 00:04:13,250
Interviewer: Were there towels?

62
00:04:13,292 --> 00:04:16,626
No, just two small towels

63
00:04:16,959 --> 00:04:18,959
And there was Zahi soap

64
00:04:19,125 --> 00:04:23,500
Showering and using the toilet were done inside

65
00:04:25,626 --> 00:04:30,042
We didn’t know our fate, whether with the air force or inside

66
00:04:31,959 --> 00:04:34,626
Interviewer: While you were here

67
00:04:34,792 --> 00:04:39,876
Did the washrooms ever break down and overflow?

68
00:04:40,751 --> 00:04:43,584
No, that didn’t happen

69
00:04:44,334 --> 00:04:48,292
Interviewer: What didn’t happen? Witness: The washrooms didn’t get clogged

70
00:04:53,459 --> 00:04:55,500
Interviewer: Let’s go back to the topic of food

71
00:04:55,584 --> 00:04:58,626
Was the food enough?

72
00:04:58,667 --> 00:05:02,792
And did you ask the guards

73
00:05:02,834 --> 00:05:05,918
To increase the amount of food?

74
00:05:05,918 --> 00:05:09,834
We couldn’t ask for anything, whether they fed us or not

75
00:05:09,959 --> 00:05:12,542
And whether we ate or not, we couldn’t ask for anything

76
00:05:14,667 --> 00:05:15,959
And you couldn’t ask any question

77
00:05:15,959 --> 00:05:19,751
We couldn’t ask for anything

78
00:05:19,792 --> 00:05:24,876
Only if the guard came and asked us, then we could speak

79
00:05:26,125 --> 00:05:27,334
And that depended on his mood

80
00:05:28,042 --> 00:05:32,209
Interviewer: You mean you didn’t ask for more food? Witness: No

81
00:05:33,083 --> 00:05:36,834
They brought food in the morning and at noon

82
00:05:36,959 --> 00:05:42,000
And most of the time the food was ready

83
00:05:46,792 --> 00:05:51,626
Interviewer: Was the place clean or did it smell?

84
00:05:51,667 --> 00:05:54,876
It was okay

85
00:05:55,167 --> 00:05:57,751
There were mattresses

86
00:05:58,584 --> 00:06:00,834
And a place for prayer and sitting

87
00:06:00,959 --> 00:06:04,459
They came to us in the morning

88
00:06:04,834 --> 00:06:09,042
We had to pray the prayers on time

89
00:06:09,292 --> 00:06:11,834
The prayers were on time, an imam led us and we stood behind him

90
00:06:11,876 --> 00:06:15,375
The imam stood, and the rest stood behind him to pray

91
00:06:16,250 --> 00:06:20,042
People were here, and there weren’t many

92
00:06:20,542 --> 00:06:24,918
Two would come in, for example, and three would leave, like that
